TextBody:
Hello Pravin,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Support.

Before we can proceed further with the case, can you please also provide us with the name of the end customer?

Regarding File Maintenance and External Storage, we recommend using audit log backups to help maintain healthy disk utilization on the EPP server and prevent the live database from becoming too large which will ultimately negatively impact EPP server performance.

For example to delete event logs older than 1 year the administrator will need to schedule an audit log backup under "System Maintenance" > "Audit Log Backup with the below configurations.




You will need to select how frequently you want the audit log backup to run. Once the backup is complete, it will be available for download at the bottom of the "Audit Log Backup" page.  Alternatively, you can choose to automatically store backups in an external shared location (a network shared folder).
To do this, you'll need to configure and map a shared location in "System Maintenance" > "External Storage" (see the second screenshot below).




I hope this information is helpful.



Kind regards
__________________
